Comment: My favourite way to start of a game.
This is a move that it is quite often countered with.
I then bring my knight out.
My opponent brings his knight out to protect his pawn on e5.
I then do this move because most people do it against me so I thought it is a good move.
Black also brings his bishop out
I then push my pawn to d3 to protect the pawn and the bishop at the same time and also opening the line of my bishop on c1.
My opponent brings their knight out so that he can castle.
I don't always do this move but sometimes people don't castle putting me in a good position.
Unfortunately, most people do castle and this is basically a beginning of a game that I have started from many times.
